rules: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, search your deck for a Basic Energy card. Show that card to your opponent, then put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Attract Current
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, you may search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Lightning Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Gigavolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage. If tails, this attack does 40 damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

abilities.name: Softboiled
abilities.text: When you play Blissey from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, remove 8 damage counters from Blissey. If tails, remove 4 damage counters from Blissey. Either way, if Blissey has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

abilities.name: Time Travel
abilities.text: If an opponent's attack would Knock Out Celebi, flip a coin. If heads, Celebi isn't Knocked Out and you shuffle it and all cards attached to it into your deck. This power doesn't work if Celebi is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Psychic Damage
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put 1 damage counter on the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Triggered Poison
attacks.text: If your opponent attaches an Energy card to the Defending Pokemon during his or her next turn, that Pokemon becomes Poisoned.

attacks.name: Cross Attack
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Present
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If exactly 1 is heads, this attack does 40 damage. If exactly 2 are heads, remove 3 damage counters from the Defending Pokemon. If the Defending Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them. If all 3 are heads, this attack does 60 damage. If all 3 are tails, remove all damage counters from the Defending Pokemon.

abilities.name: Howl
abilities.text: When you play Entei from your hand, you may discard the top 5 cards of your deck. (If you have fewer cards in your deck than that, discard all of them.) If any of those are Fire Energy cards, attach them to any of your Fire Pokemon of your choice. Using this power ends your turn.

attacks.name: Searing Flames
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy cards attached to Entei or this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Stoke
attacks.text: You may search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to Ho-Oh. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Sacred Fire
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Dive Bomb
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Dark Flame
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Houndoom or this attack does nothing. If there are any Darkness Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Houndoom.

attacks.name: Black Fang
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Darkness Energy attached to Houndoom. This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Evolutionary Spore
attacks.text: Choose any number of your Hoppips and Skiplooms. Then, for each Pokemon you chose in this way, you may search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokemon and attach it to that Pokemon. (This counts as evolving those Pokemon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

abilities.name: Electromagnetic Power
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take 1 Energy card attached to 1 of your Magnemites, Magnetons, or Dark Magnetons and attach it to a different 1 of your Magnemites, Magnetons, and Dark Magnetons. This power can't be used if Magneton is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Plasma
attacks.text: If there are any Lightning Energy cards in your discard pile, attach 1 of them to Magneton.

attacks.name: Night Eyes
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Perish Song
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is Asleep and was attacked with Night Eyes during your last turn, it is Knocked Out.

abilities.name: Energy Converter
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may choose 1 basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokemon and choose an Energy type. Treat that Energy card as that type until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Porygon2 is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. If Porygon2 becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed, the Energy card goes back to its original type.

attacks.name: Delta Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose whether the Defending Pokemon becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

abilities.name: Lightning Burst
abilities.text: Whenever you attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to Raikou, if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. This power stops working while Raikou is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Lightning Tackle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, Raikou does 20 damage to itself.

abilities.name: Crystal Body
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, other than damage, done to Suicune. This power stops working while Suicune is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Aurora Wave
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If only 1 is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

abilities.name: Prehistoric Memory
abilities.text: Whenever an Evolved Pokemon attacks (even if it's your opponent's), it can use any attack from its Basic Pokemon card or any Evolution card attached to it. It still has to pay for that attack's Energy cost. This power stops working while Aerodactyl is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Aerodactyl. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

attacks.name: Psychic Leaf
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads. Remove a number of damage counters from Celebi equal to the damage done to the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). If Celebi has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

abilities.name: Legendary Body
abilities.text: As long as Entei is your Active Pokemon, Entei and Energy cards attached to it aren't affected by effects from Trainer cards other than Stadium cards. As long as this Power is active, discard any Trainer cards attached to Entei. (This power works even if Entei is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.)

attacks.name: Mega Flame
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each tails, discard 1 Fire Energy card from Entei, if it has any.

attacks.name: Rainbow Burn
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each type of Basic Energy card, if any, attached to Ho-Oh.

attacks.name: Genetic Memory
attacks.text: Use any attack from Kingdra's Basic Pokemon card or Evolution card. (Kingdra doesn't have to pay for that attack's Energy cost.)

attacks.name: Twister
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, choose 1 Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon, if any, and discard it. If both are tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

attacks.name: Aerowing
attacks.text: You may flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 80 damage. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Lightning Strike
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Raichu. If you do, this attack does 80 damage.

abilities.name: Legendary Body
abilities.text: As long as Raikou is your Active Pokemon, Raikou and Energy cards attached to it aren't affected by effects from Trainer cards other than Stadium cards. As long as this Power is active, discard any Trainer cards attached to Raikou. (This power works even if Raikou is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.)

attacks.name: Lightning Spark
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of them and this attack does 20 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Skarmory.

attacks.name: Swipe
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard all Trainer cards attached to your opponent's Pokemon.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Core Stream
attacks.text: Choose an Energy type other than Colorless. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon with any Energy cards of that type attached to it. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

abilities.name: Mimic
abilities.text: As long as Sudowoodo is your Active Pokemon, it copies all of the Defending Pokemon's attacks, including their costs. This power can't be used if Sudowoodo is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Legendary Body
abilities.text: As long as Suicune is your Active Pokemon, Suicune and Energy cards attached to it aren't affected by effects from Trainer cards other than Stadium cards. As long as this Power is active, discard any Trainer cards attached to Suicune. (This power works even if Suicune is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.)

attacks.name: Crystal Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 30 damage and, if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Tail Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Screech
attacks.text: Until the end of your next turn, if an attack damages the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Poison Bite
attacks.text: If this attack damages the Defending Pokemon, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned and you remove a number of damage counters from Golbat equal to half that damage (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Golbat has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them. Either way, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your own Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Rock Tumble
attacks.text: Don't apply Resistance.

attacks.name: Freezing Kiss Goodnight
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Strange Dance
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, this attack does 20 damage.

abilities.name: Submerge
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may change Lanturn's type to Water until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Lanturn is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed. If Lanturn becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed after you have used this power, its type changes back to Lightning.

attacks.name: Blinding Light
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

abilities.name: Magma Pool
abilities.text: If Magcargo is your Active Pokemon and moves to the Bench, remove 1 Fire Energy card attached to Magcargo, if any, and attach it to the new Active Pokemon. (You can't choose an Energy card that you used to pay the Retreat Cost.)

attacks.name: Lava Flow
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to Magcargo when you use this attack. If you do, this attack does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Constrict
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Octazooka
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, whenever the Defending Pokemon attacks, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing. (Benching or evolving that Pokemon ends this effect.)

abilities.name: Allergic Pollen
abilities.text: As long as Parasect is in play, cards in any player's discard piles are not affected by attacks or Pokemon Powers. This power stops working if Parasect becomes Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Sleep Pinchers
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Remove 3 damage counters from Piloswine. If it has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: High-Speed Charge
attacks.text: Piloswine does 30 damage to itself. Piloswine can't use this attack during your next turn.

attacks.name: Rising Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Horn Swipe
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 40 more damage. If 1 or both of them are tails, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Terrorize
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, choose 1 of its attacks. That Pokemon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Overhead Toss
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to 1 of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Unown [B]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Bear]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name to Unown [B]. This power can't be used if Unown [B] has 10 HP left. This power can be used even if Unown [B] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [Y]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Yield]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Psychic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can be used even if Unown [Y] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Grab
attacks.text: Choose a Trainer card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Positive Ion
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Negative Ion
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon attacks Chinchou during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Chinchou is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance). (Benching or evolving either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Leek Jab
attacks.text: This attack can't be used during your next turn. (Benching Farfetch'd ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Fin Smack
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon card named Murkrow and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)

attacks.name: Flock Attack
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Murkrows on your Bench. This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Sleep Spore
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has any Energy cards attached to it, choose 1 of them and discard it.

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Needle Storm
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads you get.

attacks.name: Sharpshooting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

abilities.name: Hard Shell
abilities.text: Whenever an attack (including your own) does 40 or less damage to Shuckle (after applying Weakness and Resistance), reduce that damage to 10. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.) This power stops working while Shuckle is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Toxic Saliva
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. It now takes 20 Poison damage instead of 10 after each player's turn (even if it was already Poisoned).

attacks.name: Mysterious Powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Magma Ring
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Smoochum
rules: If this Baby Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and your opponent announces an attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything else). If tails, your opponent's turn ends.

attacks.name: Psykiss
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Raging Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Snubbull. If tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Bubblebeam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Swinub does 10 damage to itself.

name: Unown [K]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Keep]
abilities.text: Your opponent's attacks, Pokemon Powers, and Trainer cards can't discard Energy cards from your Pokemon with Unown in their names. (Any other effects still happen.)

attacks.name: Poison Spray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Balloon Berry
rules: Attach Balloon Berry to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it.
When the Pokemon Balloon Berry is attached to retreats, discard Balloon Berry instead of discarding Energy cards.

name: Healing Field
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn, he or she may flip a coin. If heads, that player removes 2 damage counters from his or her Active Pokemon (1 if it only has 1).

name: Pokemon Breeder Fields
rules: Flip a coin for 1 or 2 of your non-Baby Pokemon that can evolve. For each heads, search your deck for a later-Stage card that matches that Pokemon. Then put that card into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Rocket's Hideout
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Each Pokemon in play with Dark in its name (even your opponent's) gets +20 HP.

name: Old Rod
rules: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, put a Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, or Evolution card from your discard pile into your hand. If both are tails, put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Shining Gyarados
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Gyarados in your deck.

attacks.name: Outrage
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Shining Gyarados. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Devastate
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy cards attached to Shining Gyarados or this attack does nothing. This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Then, flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 Energy card attached to each of your opponent's Pokemon that has any Energy cards attached to it and discard those Energy cards.

name: Shining Magikarp
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Magikarp in your deck.

attacks.name: Gold Scale
attacks.text: Your opponent may draw 2 cards. Either way, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Dragon Bond
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card named Gyarados, Dark Gyarados, or Shining Gyarados. Show it to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

abilities.name: Conductivity
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent attaches an Energy card from his or her hand to a Pokemon, this power does 10 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working if you have more than 1 Dark Ampharos in play or while Dark Ampharos is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Shock Bolt
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Dark Ampharos or this attack does nothing.

abilities.name: Surprise Bite
abilities.text: When you play Dark Crobat from your hand, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This power does 20 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.)

attacks.name: Dark Drain
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each of your opponent's Pokemon. For each heads, this attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. Remove a number of damage counters from Dark Crobat equal to the damage dealt. If Dark Crobat has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Tusk Toss
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, return the Defending Pokemon and all cards attached to it to your opponent's hand. If tails, your opponent chooses 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon and switches it with the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Gouge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Psysplash
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon for each Energy card attached to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

abilities.name: Scare
abilities.text: As long as Dark Feraligatr is your Active Pokemon, all of your opponent's Baby Pokemon Powers stop working and your opponent's Baby Pokemon can't attack. This power stops working while Dark Feraligatr is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Crushing Blow
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has any Energy cards attached to it, flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of those cards and discard it.

abilities.name: Deep Sleep
abilities.text: As long as any Dark Gengar are in play, a player flips 2 coins for each of his or her Pokemon that is Asleep at the end of each turn. If either of them is tails, that Pokemon is still Asleep. This power stops working if Dark Gengar is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Pull In
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, you may choose 1 of them and switch it with the Defending Pokemon (before doing damage or other effects of this attack). Either way, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Eerie Howl
attacks.text: If your opponent's Bench isn't full, look at his or her hand. If your opponent has any Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon there, choose 1 of them and put it on his or her Bench. Then, switch it with the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Dark Fire
attacks.text: If there are any Darkness Energy cards attached to Dark Houndoom, discard 1 of them and this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage (plus 10 more damage for the Darkness Energy you discarded). If there aren't any, this attack does 30 damage.

abilities.name: Spatial Distortion
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose a Stadium card from your discard pile and put it into play. (If there's already a Stadium card in play, discard it.) This power can't be used if Dark Porygon2 is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Curve Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done by attacks to Dark Porygon2 during your opponent's next turn. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Threaten
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, look at your opponent's hand. If he or she has any Trainer cards there, choose 1 of them. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Rushing Flames
attacks.text: You may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to your Pokemon. Flip a coin for each Fire Energy card discarded in this way. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Mountain Smasher
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Fighting Energy cards attached to Dark Tyranitar. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. Then, for each heads, discard the top card from your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Fling Away
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, this attack does 30 damage instead of 50 and choose 1 of those Benched Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

abilities.name: Drive Off
abilities.text: As long as Light Arcanine is your Active Pokemon, once during your turn (before your attack), if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. This power can't be used while Light Arcanine is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Gentle Flames
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is a Baby Pokemon, this attack does 10 damage instead of 50. If the Defending Pokemon is a Basic Pokemon, this attack does 30 damage instead of 50.

attacks.name: Bubble
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Bubble Jump
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, take 2 Energy cards attached to Light Azumarill and attach them to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. Then return Light Azumarill and all cards attached to it to your hand.

abilities.name: Miraculous Wind
abilities.text: As long as Light Dragonite is your Active Pokemon, each Special Energy card provides Colorless Energy instead of its usual type and its other effects stop working. This power stops working while Light Dragonite is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Light Wave
attacks.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, other than damage, done to Light Dragonite during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Gift
abilities.text: When you play Light Togetic from your hand, your opponent may search his or her deck for a Pokemon Tool card, show that card to you, and put it into his or her hand. Either way, you may do the same, and then each player who searched shuffles his or her deck.

attacks.name: Sweet Kiss
attacks.text: Your opponent may draw a card.

name: Miracle Energy
rules: You can't have more than 1 Miracle Energy in your deck. Attach Miracle Energy to 1 of your Shining or Light Pokemon. At the end of your turn, discard Miracle Energy. While in play, Miracle Energy counts as every type of Energy but provides only 2 Energy at a time.

attacks.name: Entangle
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and switch it with the Defending Pokemon, then flip a coin. If heads, the new Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Poison Bind
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat until the end of your opponent's next turn and if the effect of an attack, Pokemon Power, or Trainer card would change that player's Active Pokemon, that part of the effect does nothing.

abilities.name: Hot Plate
abilities.text: As long as Dark Magcargo is your Active Pokemon, whenever a player puts a Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon onto his or her Bench from his or her hand, this power does 10 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.) This power stops working if Dark Magcargo is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Ball of Flame
attacks.text: You may discard a Fire Energy card attached to Dark Magcargo when you use this attack. If you do and if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 20 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Prehistoric Water
attacks.text: If your opponent has any evolved Pokemon in play, choose 1 of them and flip a coin. If heads, your opponent takes the highest Stage Evolution card on that Pokemon and shuffles it into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Dark Tentacle
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't evolve except from effects of attacks or Pokemon Powers. (Benching that Pokemon ends this effect.)

abilities.name: Cunning
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, look at the top card of your opponent's deck. Then, you may have your opponent shuffle his or her deck. This power can't be used if Dark Slowking is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: Don't apply Weakness or Resistance for this attack.

attacks.name: Provoke
attacks.text: Look at your opponent's hand. If he or she has any Baby Pokemon and/or Basic Pokemon there, you may put any number of them onto your opponent's Bench (as long as there's room). Then, your opponent looks at your hand. If you have any Baby Pokemon and/or Basic Pokemon there, your opponent may put any number of them onto your Bench (as long as there's room).

attacks.name: Battle Frenzy
attacks.text: For each Pokemon in play (yours and your opponent's), flip a coin. For each heads, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack.

attacks.name: Healing Light
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokemon that has any damage counters on it.

attacks.name: Protective Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Light Dragonair.

attacks.name: Searchlight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, each player may choose a card from his or her discard pile and put it into his or her hand.

attacks.name: Spark
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Flash Touch
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, switch 1 of them with Light Ledian. As long as that Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, it can't become Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned. (All other effects of attacks, Pokemon Powers, and Trainer cards still happen.)

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Tag Team
abilities.text: When you play Light Machamp from your hand, if it is on your Bench, remove 3 damage counters from your Active Pokemon. If it has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them. Then, switch Light Machamp with your Active Pokemon.

attacks.name: Beatdown
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has Dark in its name or is a Darkness Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 damage instead of 50.

abilities.name: Fluffy Wool
abilities.text: During your opponent's turn, if Light Piloswine is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by your opponent's attack (even if it's Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, the attacking Pokemon is now Asleep. This power stops working if Light Piloswine is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed when your opponent attacks.

attacks.name: Knock Over
attacks.text: If there is a Stadium card in play, you may discard it.

name: Unown [G]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Give]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [G], Unown [I], Unown [V], and Unown [E] on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Unown [H]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Help]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [H], Unown [E], Unown [L], and Unown [P] on your Bench, you may shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw a new hand of the same number of cards.

name: Unown [W]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Want]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [W], Unown [A], Unown [N], and Unown [T] on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Unown [X]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [XXXXX]
abilities.text: Whenever 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name uses its Hidden Power attack, flip a coin until you get tails. That attack does 10 more damage for each heads. If you have more than 1 Unown [X] in play, use only 1 [XXXXX] each turn.

attacks.name: Doubleslap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Egg Toss
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Clamping Jaw
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn. If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing. (Benching either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Triple Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: MAX Burst
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy cards attached to your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: High Voltage
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play Trainer cards during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Stun Wave
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has a Pokemon Power, that power stops working until the end of your next turn.

attacks.name: Armor Up
attacks.text: Until the end of your next turn, if Dark Forretress would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, flip a coin. If heads, Dark Forretress is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP become 10 instead.

attacks.name: Explosion
attacks.text: Dark Forretress does 60 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Call Back
attacks.text: Put a Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon card from your opponent's discard pile onto his or her Bench. Put 1 damage counter on that Pokemon. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)

attacks.name: Surround
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Water Cannon
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage for each Water Energy card attached to Dark Omanyte. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. You can't do more than 30 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Rock Tackle
attacks.text: Dark Pupitar does 10 damage to itself. Dark Pupitar can't use this attack during your next turn.

attacks.name: Explosive Evolution
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. Then, search your deck for an Evolution card named Dark Tyranitar and put it on Dark Pupitar. (This counts as evolving Dark Pupitar.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Incinerate
attacks.text: Show the top card of your opponent's deck to all players. If it's a Trainer card, discard it.

attacks.name: Rushing Magma
attacks.text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. (If there are fewer than 5 cards in your deck, discard all of them.) This attack does 20 damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Dark Song
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Slap Awake
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is Asleep or Confused, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage. Then, the Defending Pokemon is no longer Asleep or Confused.

attacks.name: Charging Horn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage. If tails, this attack does 30 damage.

attacks.name: One-Two Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Heel Drop
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Lunge
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Expand
attacks.text: All damage done to Jigglypuff during your opponent's next turn is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Freezing Breath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Ice Pillar
attacks.text: Until the end of your opponent's next turn, as long as Light Dewgong is your Active Pokemon, prevent all damage done by attacks to your Benched Pokemon. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Warm Up
attacks.text: If you have any benched Pokemon, search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of them. Then shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Burning Flame
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard a Fire Energy card attached to Light Flareon or this attack does nothing. This attack does 30 damage plus 20 damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Flipper Stroke
attacks.text: Your opponent looks at the top 3 cards of his or her deck. If any of them are basic Energy cards, he or she may show any number of them to you and put them into his or her hand. You do the same. Either way, each player shuffles his or her deck.

attacks.name: Core Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage for each Special Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Pulse Guard
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, whenever 30 or more damage is done to Light Jolteon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), prevent that damage. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Thunder Needle
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Return Home
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, shuffle 1 of them and all cards attached to it into your deck.

attacks.name: Gentle Kick
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon has no damage counters on it, this attack does 40 damage. If it has any, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Guiding Flame
attacks.text: Put a Baby Pokemon or a Basic Pokemon card from your discard pile onto your Bench. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)

attacks.name: Fire Blast
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Light Ninetales in order to use this attack.

attacks.name: Fish Out
attacks.text: Your opponent may choose up to 3 Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, and/or Evolution cards from his or her discard pile and shuffle them into his or her deck. Either way, you may do the same.

attacks.name: Splash About
attacks.text: If there are more Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon than to Light Slowbro, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage. If not, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Wash Away
attacks.text: If you have any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon and discard all Energy cards attached to it.

attacks.name: Hypnoshower
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. Remove 1 damage counter from each Benched Pokemon (yours and your opponent's) with any damage counters on it.

attacks.name: Mysterious Wing
attacks.text: Your opponent may choose a Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, or Evolution card from his or her discard pile and put it into his or her hand. Either way, you may do the same.

attacks.name: Synchronize
attacks.text: If Light Venomoth and the Defending Pokemon have a different number of Energy cards attached to them, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Evolution Song
attacks.text: Your opponent may choose 1 of his or her Pokemon and search his or her deck for a card that evolves from that Pokemon. Your opponent attaches that card to that Pokemon. This counts as evolving that Pokemon. Either way, you may do the same, and then each player who searched shuffles his or her deck.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Scyther.

attacks.name: Charm
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon attacks during your opponent's next turn, any damage it does is reduced by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Spike Ball Tackle
attacks.text: Togepi does 10 damage to itself.

name: Unown [C]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Chase]
abilities.text: As long as Unown [C] is your Active Pokemon, whenever your opponent's Active Pokemon tries to retreat, flip a coin. If heads, put 1 damage counter on that Pokemon. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

name: Unown [P]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Perform]
abilities.text: If an attack damaged Unown [P] during your opponent's last turn and Unown [P] was your Active Pokemon, Unown [P]'s Hidden Power attack does that much more damage to the Defending Pokemon. This power can be used even if Unown [P] is Confused.

name: Unown [Q]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Quicken]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to any of your Pokemon with Unown in its name during your opponent's next turn. If you have more than 1 Unown [Q] in play, use only 1 [Quicken] each turn. This power can be used even if Unown [Q] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [Z]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Zoom]
abilities.text: As long as Unown [Z] is Benched, you pay no Energy cost to retreat a Pokemon with Unown in its name.

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Ink Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Dark Octillery but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Tentacle Wrap
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, during your opponent's next turn, your opponent pays Colorless more to retreat the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Shed
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Dratini.

attacks.name: Fury Attack
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Sleep Powder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Psyshock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Nightmare
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Tail Bite
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Stun Poison
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Dodge
attacks.text: If Hitmonchan would be damaged by an attack during your opponent's next turn, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that attack's damage done to Hitmonchan. (Any other effects of attacks still happen.)

attacks.name: Leer
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn. (Benching or evolving either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Swift
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Pokemon Powers, or any other effects on the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Reflected Sunlight
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Grass Energy cards from your hand to 1 of your Grass Pokemon.

attacks.name: Giant Wave
attacks.text: Mantine can't attack during your next turn.

attacks.name: Crushing Step
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Migraine
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, Psyduck is now Confused.

attacks.name: Fury Strikes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: Seel does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Sunbathe
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from Sunkern. Search your deck for a card that evolves from Sunkern and attach that card to Sunkern. This counts as evolving Sunkern. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Generate Cold
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Totodile but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

name: Unown [L]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Laugh]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, each player shuffles his or her deck. This power can be used even if Unown [L] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [S]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Search]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may look at 1 of your Prize cards. Return that Prize card face down. This power can be used even if Unown [S] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [T]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Tell]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, look at your opponent's hand and show your hand to your opponent. This power can be used even if Unown [T] is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

name: Unown [V]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Vanish]
abilities.text: When you play Unown [V] from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokemon with Unown in its name (other than Unown [V]) to your hand. (Discard all cards attached to that card.)

attacks.name: Poisonpowder
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Vulpix in order to use this attack.

name: Broken Ground Gym
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Each player pays Colorless more to retreat a Baby Pokemon or Basic Pokemon.

name: EXP.ALL
rules: Attach EXP.ALL to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it.

During your opponent's turn, if your Active Pokemon would be Knocked Out by your opponent's attack, you may take 1 of the basic Energy cards attached to your Active Pokemon and attach it to the Pokemon with EXP.ALL attached to it. If you do, discard EXP.ALL.

name: Impostor Professor Oak's Invention
rules: Look at your opponent's Prize cards. You may have your opponent shuffle them into his or her deck. If you do, your opponent takes that many cards from the top of his or her deck and sets them aside as his or her new Prize cards (without looking at them).

name: Radio Tower
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may look at the top 2 cards of his or her deck and put them back in the same order.

name: Thought Wave Machine
rules: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, return an Energy card attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon to your opponent's hand. If the Pokemon has fewer attached Energy cards than that, return all of them to your opponent's hand. Your turn is over now (you don't get to attack).

name: Counterattack Claws
rules: Attach Counterattack Claws to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it.

During your opponent's turn, if the Pokemon Counterattack Claws is attached to is your Active Pokemon and an opponent's attack damages it (even if it is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, put 2 damage counters on the Defending Pokemon. Then, discard Counterattack Claws.

name: Energy Amplifier
rules: Choose an Energy card in your hand, show it to your opponent, and shuffle it into your deck. Then flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards. Show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Energy Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player puts a basic Energy card from his or her discard pile into his or her hand.

name: Lucky Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player draws a card.

name: Magnifier
rules: Attach Magnifier to 1 of your Pokemon. At the end of your turn, discard Magnifier. If the Pokemon Magnifier is attached to attacks, don't apply Resistance for that attack.

name: Pokemon Personality Test
rules: Put an Evolution card from your hand face down in front of you. Your opponent guesses whether it is a Pokemon card with Light in its name, a Pokemon card with Dark in its name, or neither one. Flip the card over. If your opponent guessed right, he or she draws 3 cards. If your opponent guessed wrong, you draw 3 cards. Either way, return the card to your hand.

name: Team Rocket's Evil Deeds
rules: Look at your opponent's hand and choose a card there. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck. Then, your opponent may draw up to 2 cards.

name: Heal Powder
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, your Active Pokemon is no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned and remove 2 damage counters from it. If your Active Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

name: Mail from Bill
rules: You can't play this card if you have 5 or more cards in your hand (including this one). Draw cards until you have exactly 4 cards in your hand.

name: Shining Celebi
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Celebi in your deck.

attacks.name: Healing Water
attacks.text: Remove a number of damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon equal to the number of Water Energy cards attached to Shining Celebi. If the Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Miracle Leaf
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon. If you get 1 or more heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep, Confused, or Poisoned (your choice).

name: Shining Charizard
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Charizard in your deck.

attacks.name: White-hot Flame
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card and 1 Lightning Energy card attached to Shining Charizard or this attack does nothing. Flip a coin. If tails, Shining Charizard does 30 damage to itself.

name: Shining Kabutops
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Kabutops in your deck.

attacks.name: Lightning Cut
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage and does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If tails, this attack does 30 damage and Shining Kabutops does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Water Slash
attacks.text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Shining Kabutops but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. Don't apply Resistance.

name: Shining Mewtwo
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Mewtwo in your deck.

attacks.name: Reflect Shield
attacks.text: If an attack does damage to Shining Mewtwo during your opponent's next turn (even if Shining Mewtwo is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Shining Mewtwo from that attack (any other effects of attacks still happen) and do 20 damage to the attacking Pokemon.

attacks.name: Psyburst
attacks.text: Discard a Fire Energy card attached to Shining Mewtwo or this attack does nothing. This attack does 40 damage plus 10 damage for each Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Shining Noctowl
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Noctowl in your deck.

attacks.name: Flashing Eyes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. If exactly 1 is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep. If exactly 2 are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If all 3 are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Shining Raichu
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Raichu in your deck.

attacks.name: Thundersquall
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon for each Water Energy attached to Shining Raichu. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Shining Steelix
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Steelix in your deck.

attacks.name: Crushing Earth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each Benched Pokemon (yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If tails, this attack does nothing. Either way, Shining Steelix can't attack during your next turn.

name: Shining Tyranitar
rules: You can't have more than 1 Shining Tyranitar in your deck.

attacks.name: Mountain Crush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, your opponent discards the top card from his or her deck.

attacks.name: Destructive Fire
attacks.text: Flip a coin for each Fire Energy card attached to Shining Tyranitar. For each heads, discard a Fire Energy card attached to Shining Tyranitar or this attack does nothing. Then, for each heads, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon and discard it. If it has fewer Energy cards than that, remove all of them.

abilities.name: Psymimic
abilities.text: Once during your turn, instead of Alakazam's normal attack, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon's attacks. Alakazam copies that attack including its Energy costs and anything else required in order to use that attack, such as discarding Energy cards. (No matter what type that Pokemon is, Alakazam's type is still Psychic.) This power can't be used if Alakazam is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Syncroblast
attacks.text: If Alakazam and the Defending Pokemon don't have the same number of Energy cards attached to them, this attack's base damage is 20 instead of 80.

abilities.name: Energy Connect
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may take a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Benched Pokemon and attach it to your Active Pokemon. This power can't be used if Ampharos is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Lightning Strike
attacks.text: You may discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack's base damage is 80 instead of 40.

attacks.name: Poison Spray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Poison Reaction
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

abilities.name: Jet Stream
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Blastoise is your Active Pokemon, you may flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to Blastoise, if any. Then, if there are any Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokemon, choose 1 of them and discard it. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Energy Cannon
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy Cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

abilities.name: Miraculous Powder
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove all Special Conditions from your Active Pokemon. This power can't be used if Butterfree is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Spiral Drain
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 2 damage counters from Butterfree.

abilities.name: Burning Energy
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may turn all basic Energy attached to all of your Pokemon into Fire Energy for the rest of the turn. This power can't be used if Charizard is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Scorching Whirlwind
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If 1 of them is tails, discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard. If both are tails, discard all Energy cards attached to Charizard.

abilities.name: Moonlight
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put a card from your hand back on your deck. If you do, search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Clefable is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Doubleslap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Lick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Auto Fire
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Tailwind
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Dragonite is on your Bench, you may reduce your Active Pokemon's Retreat Cost to 0.

attacks.name: Dragon Tail
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Magnitude
attacks.text: Does 10 damage to each Benched Pokemon (yours and your opponent's). (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Bill's Maintenance
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
If you have any cards in your hand, shuffle 1 of them into your deck, then draw 3 cards.

name: Copycat
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, count the number of cards in your opponent's hand and draw that many cards.

name: Dual Ball
rules: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, search your deck for a Basic Pokemon card other than a Baby Pokemon card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Energy Removal 2
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and discard it.

name: Energy Restore
rules: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, put a Basic Energy card from your discard pile into your hand. If you don't have that many basic Energy cards in your discard pile, put all of them into your hand.

name: Mary's Impulse
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, draw 2 cards.

name: Master Ball
rules: Look at 7 cards from the top of your deck. You may choose a Basic Pokemon or Evolution card from those cards, show it your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle the rest into your deck.

rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Multi Technical Machine 01.

attacks.name: Paralyzing Gaze
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Pokemon Nurse
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Remove all damage counters from 1 of your Pokemon. Then discard all Energy cards attached to it, if any.

name: Pokemon Reversal
rules: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. Flip a coin. If heads, switch that Pokemon with the Defending Pokemon.

name: Power Charge
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, shuffle 2 Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck (1 if you have only 1).

name: Professor Elm's Training Method
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for an Evolution card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Professor Oak's Research
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 5 cards.

name: Strength Charm
rules: Attach Strength Charm to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it.

Whenever an attack from the Pokemon that Strength Charm is attached to does damage (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage. At the end of your turn in which this happens, discard Strength Charm.

name: Super Scoop Up
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, return 1 of your Pokemon and all cards attached to it to your hand.

name: Warp Point
rules: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon, if any; then you switch your Active Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon, if any.

name: Energy Search
rules: Search your deck for a basic Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Full Heal
rules: Remove all Special Conditions from your Active Pokemon.

name: Moo-Moo Milk
rules: Choose 1 of your Pokemon. Flip 2 coins. Remove 2 damage counters times the number of heads from that Pokemon. If the Pokemon has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

name: Potion
rules: Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokemon (1 if that Pokemon has only 1).

name: Switch
rules: Switch your Active Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Darkness Energy
rules: If the Pokemon Darkness Energy is attached to does damage with an attack (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage. At the end of every turn, put 1 damage counter on the Pokemon Darkness Energy is attached to, unless it's Darkness or has Dark in its name. Darkness Energy provides Darkness Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Metal Energy
rules: Damage done by attacks to the Pokemon Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). If the Pokemon Metal Energy is attached to isn't Metal, whenever it damages a Pokemon by an attack, reduce that damage by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). Metal Energy provides Metal Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Apricorn Forest
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Once during each player's turn (before attacking), if that player's Bench isn't full, that player flips a coin. If heads, that player shows his or her opponent a basic Energy card from his or her hand. Then, that player searches his or her deck for a Basic Pokemon card of the same type (color) as the revealed Energy card and puts it onto his or her Bench. The player shuffles his or her deck afterward.

name: Darkness Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Darkness Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Darkness Cube 01.

attacks.name: Plunder
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard any Trainer cards attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Energy Switch
rules: Move a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Pokemon to another of your Pokemon.

name: Fighting Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Fighting Pokemon in play. That Pokemon my use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Fighting Cube 01.

attacks.name: Violent Rage
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of damage counters on this Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Fire Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Fire Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Fire Cube 01.

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Forest Guardian
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Shuffle your deck. Then, look at the top 7 cards of your deck. Choose 1 of those cards and put it into your hand. Shuffle the rest into your deck afterward.

name: Grass Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Grass Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Grass Cube 01.

attacks.name: Sleep Poison
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

name: Healing Berry
rules: Attach Healing Berry to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't already have a Pokemon Tool card attached to it. If that Pokemon is Knocked Out, discard this card.
At the end of any turn, if the Pokemon this card is attached to has 20 HP or less, remove 3 damage counters from that Pokemon and discard this card.

name: Juggler
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Discard up to 2 basic Energy cards from your hand. If you discarded 1 basic Energy card, draw 3 cards. If you discarded 2 basic Energy cards, draw 5 cards.

name: Lightning Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Lightning Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Lightning Cube 01.

attacks.name: Discharge
attacks.text: Discard all Lightning Energy cards attached to this Pokemon. Then, flip a number of coins equal to the number of Energy cards discarded that way. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

name: Memory Berry
rules: Attach Memory Berry to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't have a Pokemon Tool attached to it. If that Pokemon is Knocked Out, discard this card.

The Pokemon this card is attached to can use any attack from its Basic Pokemon card or any Evolution card from which the Pokemon evolved. (You still have to pay for that attack's Energy cost.) Discard this card at the end of any turn the Pokemon attacks.

name: Metal Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Metal Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Metal Cube 01.

attacks.name: Metal Reversal
attacks.text: Before doing damage, you may choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and switch it with the Defending Pokemon.

name: Pokemon Fan Club
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for up to 2 Baby Pokemon and/or Basic Pokemon cards and put them onto your bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Pokemon Park
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each of his or her turns, whenever a player attaches an Energy card from his or her hand to 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon, he or she removes 1 damage counter, if any, from that Pokemon.

name: Psychic Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Psychic Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may us this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Psychic Cube 01.

attacks.name: Psy Confuse
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Seer
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Look at the top 6 cards of your deck. Take all Basic Energy cards you find there, show them to your opponent, and then put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Super Energy Removal 2
rules: Flip 2 coins. If both are heads, discard all Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokemon. If both are tails, discard all Energy cards attached to your Active Pokemon. If 1 is heads and 1 is tails, this card does nothing.

name: Time Shard
rules: Attach Time Shard to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't already have a Pokemon Tool card attached to it. If that Pokemon is Knocked Out, discard this card.

If the Pokemon this card is attached to is Knocked Out by damage from the Defending Pokemon's attack during your opponent's turn, you may return up to 2 basic Energy cards attached to that Pokemon to your hand.

name: Town Volunteers
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Take 5 Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, Evolution, and/or basic Energy cards from your discard pile and then show them to your opponent. Shuffle them into your deck.

name: Traveling Salesman
rules: You can play only one Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for up to 2 Technical Machine and/or Pokemon Tool cards, show them to your opponent, and then put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Undersea Ruins
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player chooses 1 of his or her Evolved Pokemon in play and discards the top Evolution card from that Pokemon, devolving it.

name: Power Plant
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Once during each of his or her turns, a player may discard a basic Energy card from his or her hand. If that player does, he or she chooses a basic Energy card from his or her discard pile, shows it to his or her opponent, and then puts it into his or her hand.

name: Water Cube 01
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Water Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Water Cube 01.

attacks.name: Splatter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness or Resistance.

name: Weakness Guard
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokemon. Discard it at the end of your opponent's next turn.
As long as this card is attached, this Pokemon has no Weakness.

name: Darkness Energy
rules: If the Pokemon Darkness Energy is attached to damages the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), the attack does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokemon. At the end of every turn, put 1 damage counter on the Pokemon Darkness Energy is attached to, unless it's Darkness or has Dark in its name. Darkness Energy provides Darkness Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Metal Energy
rules: Damage done to the Pokemon Metal Energy is attached to is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance). If the Pokemon Metal Energy is attached to isn't Metal, whenever it damages a Pokemon, reduce that damage by 10 (before applying Weakness and Resistance). Metal Energy provides Metal Energy. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card.)

name: Rainbow Energy
rules: Attach Rainbow Energy to 1 of your Pokemon. While in play, Rainbow Energy provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card when not in play.) When you attach this card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon, put 1 damage counter on that Pokemon.

name: Boost Energy
rules: Boost Energy can be attached only to an Evolved Pokemon. Discard Boost Energy at the end of the turn it was attached. Boost Energy provides ColorlessColorlessColorless Energy. The Pokemon Boost Energy is attached to can't retreat. When the Pokemon Boost Energy is attached to is no longer an Evolved Pokemon, discard Boost Energy.

name: Crystal Energy
rules: Crystal Energy provides 1 Energy of all types (colors) of basic Energy cards attached to the Pokemon Crystal Energy is attached to. If there are no basic Energy cards attached to the Pokemon Crystal Energy is attached to, Crystal Energy provides Colorless Energy.

name: Warp Energy
rules: Warp Energy provides 1 Colorless Energy. When you attach Warp Energy from your hand to your Active Pokemon, switch your Active Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

(This effect ends if your Active Pokemon retreats or is returned to your hand.) This power can't be used if Lanturn is affected by a Special Condition.

This power can't be used if Magneton is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of the Defending Pokemon's attacks. Mini-Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required in order to use that attack.) (No matter what type the Defending Pokemon is, Togetic is still Colorless.) Togetic performs that attack.

Your opponent then draws the same number of cards from his or her deck. This power can't be used if Umbreon is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.text: If there are any damage counters on Sunkern, remove 1 of them.

attacks.name: Freezing Breath
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Rage

attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokemon. If a Pokemon has fewer damage counters than the number of heads, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Miracle Powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Condition (Asleep, Burned, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned). The Defending Pokemon is now affected by that Special Condition.

attacks.name: Supersonic
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Spin Tackle

attacks.name: Fury Attack

attacks.name: Poison Horn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.
