attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Yanma.

attacks.name: Triple Smash
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Sound Waves
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Flitter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

attacks.name: Poison Spray
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Ancient Ruins
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Once during each player's turn (before he or she attacks), if he or she has not played a Supporter card, that player may reveal his or her hand to his or her opponent. If that player reveals his or her hand and there is no Supporter card there, that player draws a card.

name: Relic Hunter
rules: You can play only 1 Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for up to 2 Supporter and/or Stadium cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Apricorn Maker
rules: You can play only 1 Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards with Ball in their names, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Crystal Shard
rules: Attach Crystal Shard to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't already have a Pokemon Tool attached to it. If that Pokemon is Knocked Out, discard this card.
As long as this card is attached to a Pokemon, that Pokemon's type (color) is Colorless. If that Pokemon attacks, discard this card at the end of the turn.

name: Desert Shaman
rules: You can play only 1 Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Shuffle your hand into your deck and draw up to 4 cards. Your opponent does the same.

name: Fast Ball
rules: Reveal cards from your deck until you reveal an Evolution card. Show that card to your opponent and put it into your hand. Shuffle the other revealed cards into your deck. (If you don't reveal an Evolution card, shuffle all the revealed cards back into your deck.)

name: Fisherman
rules: You can play only 1 Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Choose 4 basic Energy cards from your discard pile (if there are fewer basic Energy cards than choose, take all of them), show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand.

name: Friend Ball
rules: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Search your deck for a Baby Pokemon, Basic Pokemon, or Evolution card of the same type (color), show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Hyper Potion
rules: Choose 1 of your Pokemon. Discard 1 or 2 basic Energy cards attached to that Pokemon. If you discarded 1 Energy card, remove up to 3 damage counters from that Pokemon. If you discarded 2 Energy cards, remove up to 5 damage counters from that Pokemon.

name: Lure Ball
rules: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, choose an Evolution card from your discard pile, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.

name: Miracle Sphere Alpha
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Evolved Fire, Lightning, or Fighting Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Miracle Plate Alpha.

attacks.name: Fire Force
attacks.text: If the Pokemon using this attack has Fire and Lightning basic Energy cards attached to it, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If the Pokemon using this attack has Fire and Fighting basic Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage and remove 3 damage counters from the Pokemon that Miracle Plate Alpha is attached to.

name: Miracle Sphere Beta
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Evolved Fire, Water, or Psychic Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Miracle Sphere Beta.

attacks.name: Freezing Force
attacks.text: If the Pokemon using this attack has Fire and Water basic Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Burned. If the Pokemon using this attack has Water and Psychic basic Energy cards attached to it, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon, if any, and your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

name: Miracle Sphere Gamma
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Evolved Grass, Water, or Lightning Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Miracle Sphere Gamma.

attacks.name: Thunder Force
attacks.text: If the Pokemon using this attack has Grass and Lightning basic Energy cards attached to it, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned. If the Pokemon using this attack has Water and Lightning basic Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage and lets you put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Mirage Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Whenever a player tries to retreat a Pokemon during his or her turn, that player flips a coin. If heads, that player retreats that Pokemon (and discards Energy normally). If tails, that Pokemon can't retreat this turn (the player doesn't discard any Energy).

name: Mystery Plate Alpha
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Mystery Plate Alpha.

attacks.name: Desert Burn
attacks.text: If your opponent has 5 or more Prizes, search your deck for a Trainer card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. If your opponent has only 1 Prize, the Defending Pokemon is now Burned, Paralyzed, and Poisoned.

name: Mystery Plate Beta
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Mystery Plate Beta.

attacks.name: Stone Crush
attacks.text: If your opponent has 5 or more Prizes, draw 3 cards. If your opponent has only 1 Prize, choose 2 Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokemon (1 if there is only 1). Your opponent shuffles those cards into his or her deck.

name: Mystery Plate Gamma
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Mystery Plate Gamma.

attacks.name: Retro Cave
attacks.text: If your opponent has 5 or more Prizes, shuffle your hand into your deck and then draw 6 cards. If your opponent has exactly 2 Prizes, choose 1 of your opponent's Evolved Pokemon. Your opponent puts the top card on that Evolved Pokemon on the bottom of his or her deck. (This counts as devolving that Pokemon.)

name: Mystery Plate Delta
rules: Attach this card to 1 of your Pokemon in play. That Pokemon may use this card's attack instead of its own. At the end of your turn, discard Mystery Plate Delta.

attacks.name: Healing Oasis
attacks.text: If your opponent has 5 or more Prizes, search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward. If your opponent has exactly 2 Prizes, remove all damage counters from 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Mystery Zone
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.

Once during each player's turn (before he or she attacks), if that player has an Evolution card in his or her hand, he or she may search his or her deck for a basic Energy card, show it to his or her opponent, and put it into his or her hand. Then that player chooses an Evolution card from his or her hand, shows it to his or her opponent, and puts it into his or her deck. That player shuffles his or her deck afterward.

name: Oracle
rules: You can play only 1 Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Choose 2 cards from your deck and shuffle the rest of your deck. Put the chosen cards on top of your deck in any order.

name: Star Piece
rules: Attach Star Piece to 1 of your Pokemon that doesn't already have a Pokemon Tool attached to it. If that Pokemon is Knocked Out, discard this card.

At any time between turns, if the Pokemon this card is attached to is Benched and has 2 or more damage counters on it, search your deck for an Evolution card that Pokemon evolves into and put it on top of that Pokemon. (This counts as evolving that Pokemon.) Shuffle your deck afterward. Then, discard Star Piece.

name: Underground Expedition
rules: You can play only 1 Supporter card each turn. When you play this card, put it next to your Active Pokemon. When your turn ends, discard this card.
Look at the bottom 4 cards of your deck. Put 2 of those cards into your hand, and then return the remaining cards to the bottom of your deck in any order.

name: Underground Lake
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn, that player may put an Omanyte or a Kabuto card from his or her discard pile onto his or her Bench. (Cards put on the Bench this way are considered Basic Pokemon.)

name: Bounce Energy
rules: This card provides ColorlessColorless Energy. You can attach this card to your Pokemon that has basic Energy cards attached to it. When you play this card from your hand and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon, return a basic Energy card attached to that Pokemon to your hand.

name: Cyclone Energy
rules: This card provides Colorless Energy. When you play this card from your hand and attach it to your Active Pokemon, your opponent switches his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Retro Energy
rules: This card provides Colorless Energy. When you play this card from your hand and attach it to 1 of your Evolved Pokemon, you may remove up to 2 damage counters from that Pokemon and discard the top card from it. (This counts as devolving it.)

If you do, put damage counters equal to the amount of Energy cards removed in this way on any number of your opponent's Benched Pokemon in the way you like. (For example, if you discard 3 Lightning Energy cards, you can put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and 2 on another.)

attacks.name: Bounce Off

attacks.text: Choose up to 2 Energy cards from your discard pile and attach them to Mewtwo.

attacks.name: Recharge
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Pikachu. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy cards attached to Pikachu in order to use this attack.

abilities.name: Special Delivery
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may draw a card. If you do, choose a card from your hand and put it on top of your deck. This power can't be used if Dragonite is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Supersonic Flight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Flames of Rage
attacks.text: Discard 2 Fire Energy cards attached to Arcanine in order to use this attack. This attack does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Arcanine.

attacks.name: First Aid
attacks.text: Remove 1 damage counter from Jigglypuff.

attacks.name: Double-edge
attacks.text: Jigglypuff does 20 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Psywave
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Devolution Beam
attacks.text: Choose an evolved Pokemon (your own or your opponent's). Return the highest Stage Evolution card on that Pokemon to its player's hand. That Pokemon is no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned, or anything else that might be the result of an attack (just as if you had evolved it).

attacks.name: Psywave
attacks.text: Does 10 damage times the number of Energy cards attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Devolution Beam
attacks.text: Choose an evolved Pokemon (your own or your opponent's). Return the highest Stage Evolution card on that Pokemon to its player's hand. That Pokemon is no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned, or anything else that might be the result of an attack (just as if you had evolved it).

attacks.name: Cat Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage. If tails and if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and this attack does 20 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

abilities.name: Chain Reaction
abilities.text: This power can only be used when a Pokemon evolves. Search your deck for a card that evolves from Eevee and attach it to Eevee. This counts as evolving Eevee. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Eevee is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Energy Control
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and attach it to another of your opponent's Pokemon of your choice.

attacks.name: Telekinesis
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

abilities.name: Solar Power
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Your Active Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon are no longer Asleep, Confused, Paralyzed, or Poisoned. This power can't be used if Venusaur is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Remove a number of damage counters from Venusaur equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance) (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Venusaur has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.

attacks.name: Energy Absorption
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 Energy cards from your discard pile and attach them to Mewtwo.

attacks.name: Texture Magic
attacks.text: You may change Cool Porygon's Resistance to a type of your choice other than Colorless. If the Defending Pokemon has a Weakness, you may change it to a type of your choice other than Colorless. (Benching either Pokemon ends the effect on that Pokemon.)

attacks.name: 3-D Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Computer Error
rules: You may draw up to 5 cards, then your opponent may draw up to 5 cards. Your turn is over now (you don't get to attack).

attacks.name: Tempt
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and switch it with the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Poison Claws
attacks.text: Flip a coin. if heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Miraculous Comeback
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Pokemon in play. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads. Then Team Rocket's Meowth does 10 damage times the number of tails to itself.

attacks.name: Synchronize
attacks.text: This attack can't be used unless Sabrina's Abra and the Defending Pokemon have the same number of Energy cards attached to them.

attacks.name: Headache
attacks.text: Your opponent can't play Trainer cards during his or her next turn.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Hyper Flame
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Moltres. If tails, discard all Energy cards attached to Moltres. If you can't discard Energy cards, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Diamond Dust
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed and this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Lightning Burn
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, and if your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If tails, Zapdos does 30 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Birthday Surprise
attacks.text: If it's not your birthday, this attack does 30 damage. If it is your birthday, flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 50 more damage; if tails, this attack does 30 damage.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Flying Pikachu; if tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

attacks.name: Thunderbolt
attacks.text: Discard all Energy cards attached to Pikachu.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Pikachu.

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to Marill but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Snivel
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokemon attacks Togepi during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Togepi is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance). (Benching either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Mini-Metronome
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of the Defending Pokemon's attacks. Mini-Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else in order to use that attack.) (No matter what type the Defending Pokemon is, Togepi's type is still Colorless.) Togepi performs that attack.

name: Cleffa
rules: If this Baby Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and your opponent announces an attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything else). If tails, your opponent's turn ends.

attacks.name: Eek
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Paint
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a type (other than Colorless) and put a Coloring counter on the Defending Pokemon. That Pokemon is now the type you chose. If it already had a Coloring counter, remove the old one. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Leer
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't attack Scizor during your opponent's next turn. (Benching either Pokemon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Metal Pincer
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

abilities.name: Bolt
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent's attack damages Entei, unless that attack Knocks Out Entei, flip a coin. If heads, shuffle Entei and all cards attached to it into your deck. This power can't be used if Entei is already Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed when it is damaged.

attacks.name: Protective Flame
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to your Benched Pokemon.

name: Pichu
rules: If this Baby Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and your opponent announces an attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything else). If tails, your opponent's turn ends.

attacks.name: Let's Play!
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Baby Pokemon card and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. (You can't use this attack if your Bench is full.)

name: Igglybuff
rules: If this Baby Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and your opponent announces an attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything else). If tails, your opponent's turn ends.

attacks.name: Good Night Song
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Repeating Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Rapid Spin
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with his or her Active Pokemon, then, if you have any Benched Pokemon, you switch 1 of them with your Active Pokemon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokemon.)

name: Unown [J]
rules: You may have up to 4 Basic Pokemon cards in your deck with Unown in their names.

abilities.name: [Join]
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown [J], Unown [O], Unown [I], and Unown Dragon on your Bench, you may search your deck for a Basic Pokemon or Evolution card. Show that card to your opponent, then put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Pain Split
attacks.text: Put 1 damage counter on the Defending Pokemon for each damage counter on Misdreavus.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Pokemon Center
rules: Remove all damage counters from all of your own Pokemon with damage counters on them, then discard all Energy cards attached to those Pokemon.

name: Lucky Stadium
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Once during each player's turn (before attacking), that player may flip a coin. If heads, that player draws a card.

name: Pokemon Tower
rules: This card stays in play when you play it. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
If the effect of a Pokemon Power, attack, Energy card, or Trainer card would put a card in a discard pile into its owner's hand, that card stays in that discard pile instead.

attacks.name: Seething Anger
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of damage counters on Machamp. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Fling
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokemon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Burning Fire
attacks.text: When you use this attack, you may discard any number of Fire Energy cards attached to your Pokemon in play. This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Fire Energy card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Slashing Strike
attacks.text: Scyther can't use this attack during your next turn. (Benching or evolving Scyther ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Lightning Rod
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and put a Lightning Rod marker on it. (A Pokemon can have only 1 Lightning Rod marker on it at a time.)

attacks.name: Lightning Bolt
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to any Pokemon with a Lightning Rod marker on it. Apply Weakness and Resistance.

abilities.name: Neutral Shield
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Mew by Evolved Pokemon. You can't use this power if Mew is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Psyshock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

abilities.name: Aurora Veil
abilities.text: As long as Articuno is your Active Pokemon, your Benched Pokemon do not take damage from and are not affected by attacks. This power cannot be used if Articuno is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

abilities.name: Guard
abilities.text: As long as Snorlax is your Active Pokemon, the Defending Pokemon can't Retreat. This power stops working when Snorlax is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Roll Over
attacks.text: Snorlax is now Asleep. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Leaf Slice
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Jump Over
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokemon, choose 1 of them. Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Super Singe
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Sacred Wing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack's base damage is 20 instead of 60.

abilities.name: Pure Body
abilities.text: To attach a Water Energy card from your hand to Suicune, you must discard an Energy card attached to Suicune. (Attach the Water Energy, and then discard an Energy card from Suicune.)

attacks.name: Hypno Wave
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 20 more damage. If tails, this attack does 30 damage and the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Thundershock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Thunderpunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 10 more damage; if tails, this attack does 30 damage plus Electabuzz does 10 damage to itself.

name: Professor Elm
rules: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 7 cards. You can't play any more Trainer cards this turn.

attacks.name: Focus
attacks.text: During your next turn, Rocket's Scizor's Agility attack's damage is doubled.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Rocket's Scizor.

attacks.name: Entrap
attacks.text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Continuous Scratch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

abilities.name: Vine Pull
abilities.text: Once during your turn when Dark Ivysaur retreats, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and switch it with his or her Active Pokemon.

attacks.name: Fury Strikes
attacks.text: Your opponent puts 3 markers onto his or her Pokemon (divided as he or she chooses). (More than 1 marker can be put on the same Pokemon.) Then, this attack does 10 damage to each Pokemon for each marker on it. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance. Remove the markers at the end of the turn.

attacks.name: Horrid Pollen
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If 1 is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned. If both are heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned. If both are tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

attacks.name: Juxtapose
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch the number of damage counters on Rocket's Mewtwo with the number of damage counters on the Defending Pokemon (even if it would Knock Out either Pokemon). (It's okay if 1 of the Pokemon has no damage counters on it.)

attacks.name: Hypnoblast
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Crosscounter
attacks.text: If an attack does damage to Rocket's Hitmonchan during your opponent's next turn (even if Rocket's Hitmonchan is Knocked Out), flip a coin. If heads, Rocket's Hitmonchan attacks your opponent's Active Pokemon for double that amount of damage. (If Rocket's Hitmonchan takes 20 damage, it does 40 damage to that Pokemon.)

attacks.name: Rainbow Wave
attacks.text: Choose a type of Energy other than Colorless attached to Mew. This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon of that type (including Benched Pokemon). Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Supersonic Flight
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Bawl
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Strange Scent
attacks.text: Each player flips a coin. Each player who gets heads chooses a total of 3 damage counters from among his or her Pokemon and removes them. (If the player's Pokemon have fewer total damage counters than that, he or she removes all of them.)

attacks.name: Sharp Teeth
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Agility
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Ledyba.

attacks.name: Tempting Eyes
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and switch it with the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Sing
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Fly
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Butterfree. If tails, this attack does nothing (not even damage).

attacks.name: Rainbow Powder
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Tentacle Grip
attacks.text: Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Water Energy attached to Tentacruel. For each heads, draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Squirt
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Gentle Song
attacks.text: If Lapras has any damage counters on it, remove 2 of them from it (1 if it only has 1). If the Defending Pokemon has any damage counters on it, remove 2 of them from it (1 if it only has 1). The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Ice Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Sharpshooter
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Flip a number of coins equal to the number of Grass Energy attached to Exeggutor. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Revelation
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for a Trainer card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Wartortle but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

attacks.name: Lick Wounds
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 Pokemon (yours or your opponent's) with damage counters on it and remove 2 damage counters from it (1 if it only has 1).

attacks.name: Tongue Stretch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.

attacks.name: Paradise Pollen
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 2 damage counters from Vileplume (1 if it only has 1). Then, if you have any Benched Pokemon with damage counters on them, choose 1 of them and remove 2 damage counters from it (1 if it only has 1).

attacks.name: Horrid Pollen
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed. If tails, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Rampage
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Primeape. Flip a coin. If tails, Primeape is now Confused (after doing damage).
